An infrared camera has captured footage of a rare wild giant panda and her cub in Fengtongzhai National Nature Reserve in southwest China's Sichuan Province.The video filmed on June 20, 2022, showed the mother panda drinking from a pond when the cub, estimated about nine months old, playfully approached the mother. The mother and the cub snuggled near the pond before walking off together.Fengtongzhai National Nature Reserve, part of China's Giant Panda National Park, has recorded many traces of wild giant panda mothers and cubs over the past few years.The status of wild giant pandas in China was downgraded from "endangered" to "vulnerable" last July as the population had grown from 1,114 to 1,864 over the past four decades following improved environmental protection efforts. (Cover image via screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)